---
// src/pages/privacy-policy.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy | BrandsBuilders Agency',
  description:
    'How we collect, use and protect personal information. Form-first intake, minimal tracking, consent aligned to PIPEDA/CASL. Client-owned accounts.',
  canonical: 'https://brandsbuilders.agency/privacy-policy'
};

const lastUpdated = '2025-10-13';
const contactEmail = 'hello@brandsbuilders.agency';
---
<Layout seo={seo}>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative py-24 lg:py-32 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-950 via-slate-900 to-violet-950"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20">
      <div class="absolute top-1/4 left-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-600 to-purple-600 rounded-full mix-blend-multiply filter blur-xl animate-pulse"></div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-80 h-80 bg-gradient-to-br from-fuchsia-600 to-pink-600 rounded-full mix-blend-multiply filter blur-xl animate-pulse"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
      <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-bold mb-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-white via-violet-200 to-fuchsia-200 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 mb-4">
          Your privacy matters. This explains what we collect, why, and your choices.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-400">
          Last updated: <span class="text-violet-400">{lastUpdated}</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-slate-950 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-5">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width=60 height=60 viewBox=0 0 60 60 xmlns=http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%3E%3Cg fill=none fill-rule=evenodd%3E%3Cg fill=%23a855f7 fill-opacity=0.4%3E%3Ccircle cx=30 cy=30 r=1/%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/svg%3E')] bg-repeat"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="glass rounded-3xl p-8 lg:p-12">
          <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none privacy-content">

            <p class="text-slate-300">
              We operate a form-first intake and a Free 72-Hour Growth Sprint. We aim for minimal tracking, consent by default, and client-owned accounts wherever possible.
            </p>

            <h2>1. Who We Are & Roles</h2>
            <p><strong>BrandsBuilders Agency</strong> (Alberta, Canada). For most activities, we act as a <strong>service provider/processor</strong> to our clients; for this website and our own outreach, we act as a <strong>controller</strong>.</p>

            <h2>2. What We Collect</h2>
            <h3>Information you provide</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Application forms</strong> (e.g., Free 72-Hour Sprint, Growth Partner): name, email/phone, company, website, city/industry, goals, preferred contact, and access preferences.</li>
              <li><strong>Contact</strong>: messages sent to <strong>{contactEmail}</strong> or through our site.</li>
              <li><strong>Newsletter</strong>: email address and consent status.</li>
              <li><strong>Project delivery</strong>: credentials/roles you grant in client-owned accounts (e.g., GA4, GSC, ad platforms, hosting).</li>
              <li><strong>Billing</strong>: processed by third-party providers; we don’t store full payment details.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Information we generate or observe</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Loom previews</strong> for the free sprint using public data/screens; no private access required until you approve.</li>
              <li><strong>Technical</strong>: IP, device, browser, pages, referrers, time on site; collected only to the extent needed for security/analytics.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Review applications, qualify fit, and operate the Free 72-Hour Growth Sprint.</li>
              <li>Deliver Growth Partner services (web, Local SEO/GBP, paid media, measurement).</li>
              <li>Communicate by email/phone/text when you consent or when reasonably expected to fulfil your request (CASL).</li>
              <li>Security, debugging, and improving our site and processes.</li>
              <li>Legal compliance and record-keeping.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Legal Basis / Consent (PIPEDA &amp; CASL)</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Consent:</strong> intake forms use explicit consent for contact; newsletter uses opt-in with unsubscribe in every email.</li>
              <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> running a secure site, preventing abuse, and replying to your inquiries.</li>
              <li>You may withdraw consent anytime via links provided or by emailing <strong>{contactEmail}</strong>.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Cookies & Tracking</h2>
            <p>We avoid heavy third-party tracking. By default we use:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Essential</strong> (required for forms/security).</li>
              <li><strong>Light analytics</strong> to understand usage (aggregated/limited retention). We prefer first-party or privacy-respecting tools.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You can control cookies in your browser. We do not run interest-based ad trackers on this site.</p>

            <h2>6. Sharing</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Service providers</strong>: hosting/CDN, form handling (e.g., Netlify Forms/Typeform/Google Forms), email delivery, analytics, billing, project tools—under contracts and only for the stated purposes.</li>
              <li><strong>Access you grant</strong>: collaborator/manager roles in your client-owned accounts (you can remove us anytime).</li>
              <li><strong>Legal</strong>: when required by law or to protect rights, security, and integrity.</li>
              <li>No sale of personal information.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>7. Retention</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Form submissions</strong>: up to 12 months for non-clients or until you request deletion.</li>
              <li><strong>Client records</strong>: for the engagement + up to 24 months post-project (or longer if law requires).</li>
              <li><strong>Analytics logs</strong>: shortest feasible period, typically 90–180 days in aggregated form.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You may request access, correction, deletion, or portability, and object/withdraw consent to marketing. We aim to respond within 30 days. Contact: <strong>{contactEmail}</strong>.</p>

            <h2>9. International Transfers</h2>
            <p>We may use providers with servers in Canada, the U.S., or elsewhere. We apply contractual and technical safeguards appropriate to the sensitivity of the data.</p>

            <h2>10. Security</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>HTTPS/SSL, role-based access, least privilege.</li>
              <li>Secrets stored in client-owned systems where possible; audit of collaborator access.</li>
              <li>Vendor due diligence and periodic reviews.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>11. Children</h2>
            <p>Our services are not directed to individuals under 18. If we learn we collected data from a minor, we’ll delete it.</p>

            <h2>12. Third-Party Links</h2>
            <p>External sites have their own policies. Review them before sharing information.</p>

            <h2>13. Free 72-Hour Growth Sprint Notes</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Application form filters fit and provides baseline info.</li>
              <li>Initial Loom uses only public data; implementation requires temporary access you control.</li>
              <li>Daily updates and a final before→after Loom are delivered; scope is intentionally narrow.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>14. Hours & Contact Preferences</h2>
            <p>Operating hours: <strong>9:00 AM – 9:00 PM, seven days a week (Alberta)</strong>. You can choose email, phone, or text as your preferred channel on our forms and can change this anytime.</p>

            <h2>15. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this policy. Material changes will be posted here with the updated date above.</p>

            <h2>16. Contact</h2>
            <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded-2xl p-6 mt-6">
              <p><strong>BrandsBuilders Agency</strong><br />
              Alberta, Canada<br />
              Email: <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`} class="text-violet-300 underline underline-offset-2">{contactEmail}</a></p>
            </div>

            <h2>17. Compliance Statement</h2>
            <p>This policy is designed to align with Canadian privacy law, including <strong>PIPEDA</strong>, and with international best practices (e.g., GDPR principles) where applicable. For marketing, we follow <strong>CASL</strong> (opt-in, clear identification, easy unsubscribe).</p>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact CTA -->
        <div class="glass rounded-3xl p-8 text-center mt-12">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Questions About Your Privacy?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6">
            We’ll respond by email. Reach us at <span class="text-violet-300 font-semibold">{contactEmail}</span>.
          </p>
          <a
            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-8 py-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-600 to-purple-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-2xl hover:from-violet-700 hover:to-purple-700 transition-all duration-300 transform hover:scale-105"
          >
            Email {contactEmail}
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 12H8m8 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4"></path>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(139 92 246 / 0.3);
  }
  .privacy-content h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .privacy-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: rgb(196 181 253);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .privacy-content p {
    color: rgb(203 213 225);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .privacy-content ul {
    color: rgb(203 213 225);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .privacy-content li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .privacy-content strong { color: rgb(196 181 253); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
